    "body": "### Language server\n\n_No response_\n\n### Requested feature\n\nI could not find documentation as of how to set a language server as optional and toggle it on and off without restarting Neovim.\r\n\r\nI think this is a common use case and it would be nice to have it documented.\r\n\r\nThis could easily be achieved by setting `autostart` to `false` and using `:LspStart`.\r\n\r\nExample: set `pylsp` as optional and toggle it on manually:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\n-- init.lua\r\nrequire('lspconfig').pylsp.setup {\r\n    autostart = false,\r\n    settings = {\r\n        pylsp = {\r\n            plugins = {\r\n                flake8 = {\r\n                    enabled = true,\r\n                },\r\n            },\r\n        },\r\n    },\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nUsing the above setup, PyLSP would not be started even if a `py` file is open.\r\n\r\nOne would toggle it on using `:LspStart pylsp`.\n\n### Other clients which have this feature\n\n_No response_",
